      • makeJavaDocClass

        public JavaDocClass makeJavaDocClass(java.lang.String name,
                            java.lang.String text,
                            java.lang.String deprecated,
                            java.lang.String since,
                            java.lang.String see,
                            java.lang.String author,
                            java.lang.String version)
        Creates an instance of JavaDocClass from given String values. It supposes special format of some parameters.
        Parameters:
        name - Class name.
        text - JavaDoc element text.
        deprecated - If this String is not empty, JavaDoc class will be deprecated.
        since - Value of since annotation.
        see - Values of see annotation. This String should have been empty or containing values separated by ','.
        author - Values of author annotation. This String should have been empty or containing values separated by ','.
        version - Value of version annotation.
        Returns:
        New instance of JavaDocClass with attributes generated from given parameters.

      • makeJavaDocMethod

        public JavaDocMethod makeJavaDocMethod(java.lang.String name,
                              java.lang.String comment,
                              java.lang.String deprecated,
                              java.lang.String since,
                              java.lang.String see,
                              java.util.List<java.lang.String> parameters,
                              java.lang.String returns)
        Creates an instance of JavaDocMethod from given String values. It supposes special format of some parameters.
        Parameters:
        name - Class name.
        comment - JavaDoc element text.
        deprecated - If this String is not empty, JavaDoc class will be deprecated.
        since - Value of since annotation.
        see - Values of see annotation. This String should have been empty or containing values separated by ','.
        parameters - List of String representation of parameters. Every parameter is formed by parameter's name and parameter's description. These two parts are divided by char value '-'.
        returns - Value of return annotation.
        Returns:
        New instance of JavaDocMethod with attributes generated from given parameters.
